2. Step one , create 200 sprite3D objs and remove after 2 sec . Then run it again and again , the memory increasing
3. The question may be in Physics3DShape::initMesh , in there
    auto mesh = new btTriangleMesh(false);
the variable mesh , I didn't found released any where

Running on Windows OS the application stops after the `Application::run()` return error. But on Android OS it continue working.
Investigation shows that you just ignore the result of `Application::run()` here:
https://github.com/cocos2d/cocos2d-x/blob/04fd2b16b2a3a430965b9d9151badf25cd972a15/cocos/platform/android/javaactivity-android.cpp#L95

``` .cpp
cocos2d::Application::getInstance()->run();
```

This string must be changed like that:

``` .cpp
if( cocos2d::Application::getInstance()->run() == 0 )
{
    director->end();
    return;
};
```

So the application will be terminated after failed startup.

The condition `cocos2d::Application::getInstance()->run() == 0` selected due to next code:
https://github.com/cocos2d/cocos2d-x/blob/04fd2b16b2a3a430965b9d9151badf25cd972a15/cocos/platform/android/CCApplication-android.cpp#L69
